          <h2>Pagination</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Pagination appears when there are more than 15 products on the PLP. Pagination varies depending on the device you are using.<br>
              <b>Desktop (and tablet landscape)</b> the pagination is presented as: Prev (Up to 5 characters e.g. 12345 or 1...3..5) Next> 
              <b>Mobile (and tablet portrait)</b> the pagination is just: &lt; Prev Next &gt;
            </p>
            <h4>Interactions</h4>
            <p>Users can click pagination links to sort through list</p>
            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There are three layout modes: desktop, tablet and mobile. Larger screens utilise a horizontal layout with up to 5 numbered elements displayed in the pagination list. Tablet screens remove the numbered items and show prev/next buttons. Smaller screens only display the smaller subset of buttons at the bottom of the screen.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <h4>Media queries</h4>
            <p>We are using three breakpoints to handle the changes between desktop, tablet and mobile. Common styles are loaded for the component and then device specific styles are loaded in for each breakpoint into the appropriate stylesheet.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/pagination.scss</p>
            <p>/large-components/pagination.scss</p>
            <p>/tablet-components/pagination.scss</p>
            <p>/small-components/pagination.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Use of JavaScript</h3>
            <p>JavaScript facilitates updating the page with new product results when a page is selected, and the 'show all' infinite scroll functionality.</p>
            <h4>Use of AJAX</h4>
            <p>Whenever a user clicks a page link, an AJAX request is sent. The endpoint needs to be integrated with the back end. See clubcard.listing.setCurrentPage(). The response must be an HTML partial containing the new pagination and products - see partials/ajax-listing-page.html for an example.</p>
            <p>If the user clicks 'show all', the next page is automatically requested when scrolling to the bottom of the list. The user can revert back to the paginated version by clicking the link again. The data-total-pages attribute must be set on the listings container in order to prevent the script requesting more pages than are available.</p>
            <h4>Non-JS behaviour</h4>
            <p>The Show All link is not displayed. Infintie scroll functionality is not available.</p>
